  "response_text": "A pale yellow vintage convertible drives along a wide, open country road bordered by low fields, utility poles, and a cloudy sky. The white Spotify Premium logo appears over the left side of the image. The car is shown with its roof down, carrying several passengers dressed in old-fashioned, formal-looking outfits: pale jackets, ruffled sleeves, jewelry, and grey curled wigs like powdered court wigs. From behind, the passengers sit shoulder to shoulder across the open car, raising their hands and moving as if enjoying the ride.\n\nA closer view reveals a Black adult man in the front seat wearing a curled grey wig, a pale gold jacket, and layered pearl-like necklaces. His face is calm and focused, tilted slightly upward in the sunlight. Around him, other passengers, including younger people, wear similar curled wigs and ornate pale clothing. Seen through the windshield, the group fills the convertible: a young passenger sits at the front left, two younger passengers sit behind, and the adult man drives on the right, all still in the stylized eighteenth-century look.\n\nThe focus shifts to a smartphone held in a hand with long, pale nails. The screen shows the Spotify app with a dark background, a portrait near the top, and the large text “This is Leikeli47.” A green play button sits in the center of the screen, and a finger taps it, visually showing music being selected in Spotify.\n\nBack in the convertible, the occupants now appear in modern clothing instead of powdered wigs and formal costumes. A Black adult man drives, wearing a soft pink hoodie, while a Black adult woman sits in the front passenger seat with her hair styled high and braided, wearing a patterned jacket. Two girls sit in the back in pastel jackets, one light blue and one pink. The family rides together in the same yellow convertible, moving and bobbing in their seats as if reacting to what is playing. The driver keeps one hand on the steering wheel while the others look down, forward, or toward each other in relaxed, absorbed poses.\n\nThe car is then seen from the side as someone in patterned pastel clothing steps out beside it. White promotional text appears over the scene: “The Spotify family plan.” Fine print along the bottom reads that it includes six Premium accounts for family members under one roof and that terms apply. The text expands to read: “The Spotify family plan. Six accounts. Just $14.99/mo.” The background remains bright and sunlit, with the yellow car at left and a person walking away to the right.\n\nTwo children in pastel outfits enter through sliding glass doors with bold red horizontal bars. They wear soft pink and lavender clothing, with high bun hairstyles and padded coats, and they step inside together as if arriving somewhere public, possibly a diner or roadside stop. White text on the left reads, “Get the kids on Leikeli47.” More family members follow behind them, also dressed in coordinated pink and lavender tones. The children move forward with confident, playful steps, one holding the door and another swinging an arm as they pass through.\n\nThe scene changes to a counter inside a bright restaurant-like space. A group of people, including children and at least one adult man with a beard, lean toward the counter wearing black caps with white block lettering, black leather-style jackets, and black gloves. White text reads, “Get the kids on Janet.” They look forward with serious, performance-like expressions, clustered shoulder to shoulder as if posing or preparing to order.\n\nAnother child appears in a blue shark costume. The costume has a white belly and a hood shaped like a shark’s open mouth, with white triangular “teeth” around the child’s face. The child sticks out their tongue playfully. White text reads, “Get the kids on Baby Shark.” Behind them is a chalkboard-style menu listing playful food names, including “Spiced Baby Carrots,” “K Pop Corn Chicken,” and “Pineapple Sponge Cake.”\n\nA group of four people then crowd around what looks like a display case or counter, all dressed in bright yellow, SpongeBob-inspired outfits. A child on the left wears a cap and glasses; a bearded adult man beside them smiles widely; another child in the middle wears a white sailor-style hat and a square yellow costume panel; an adult man on the right leans in with an excited open-mouthed expression. Several hands are raised against or near the glass, and the white text reads, “Get the kids on SpongeBob.”\n\nNext, four people stand in a row in a bright indoor space, dressed in country-western, Dolly Parton-inspired outfits. They wear blonde wigs, pink cowboy hats, pink or cream jackets, fringe, embroidery, and coordinated western details. The white text at left reads, “Get the kids on Dolly.” One girl in the center, wearing a vivid pink cowgirl outfit with white fringe, looks forward and gestures with her hands, while the others stand posed beside her.\n\nOutside in a parking lot, a child appears in a Lady Gaga-inspired look. They wear a short curled blonde wig, oversized black cat-eye sunglasses, and a dramatic black-and-white sculptural outfit with large pointed panels extending from the shoulders like wings or a bow. White text reads, “Get the kids on Gaga.” The child turns away, showing the back of the angular costume. Fine print along the bottom again mentions the family plan price, six Premium accounts, one roof, and terms.\n\nThe on-screen message changes to “Get the kids on the new Spotify Kids App.” Colorful curved lines and dots in yellow, pink, and green animate around the words. In the background, a low roadside building and a sign reading “FAMILY PAN” are visible, with a mostly empty parking lot and flat open landscape beyond. More people in matching black-and-white striped sculptural outfits move through the parking lot, their oversized shoulder shapes echoing the Gaga-style costume. Some are closer to the viewer, partially blocking the text as they pass, while smaller